eedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Mai 02, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fxu1701663302440.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fxu1701663302440.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fxu1701663302440.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fxu1701663302440\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">web.ini</code> file defines the physical UX web widget definitions where\n\t\tevery section is a single widget definition. Each widget definition includes the name of the\n\t\twidget class that implements the client (browser) side of the widget, the JavaScript,\n\t\tModule, and CSS files that are required to run the widget class, some placeholder layout\n\t\tHTML used by the IDE and IDE property definitions, IncludeScript which refers to the widget\n\t\tspecific ProcScript or JavaScript fragments to be included and the Interface Version using\n\t\twhich the widget is implemented.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fxu1701663302440__DraftDocumentationUnifaceUX-DefaultLocation\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d648608e52\">Default Location</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Depends on the value specified by the <span class=\"ph filepath\">/adm</span> switch.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">web.ini </code>file is located in <code class=\"ph codeph\">/uniface/adm </code>in your\n\t\t\t\tUniface installation folder.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fxu1701663302440__section_llc_sjr_qzb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d648608e73\">File Sections</h2>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"fxu1701663302440__ul_zbp_rjr_qzb\">\n<li class=\"li\"><em class=\"ph i\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qyo1701663851047.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qyo1701663851047.html\" title=\"This section, as defined in the web.ini file, defines a single physical UX web widget for Dynamic Server Page (DSP) components, including the name of the widget class that implements the client (browser) side of the widget, the JavaScript, Module, and CSS URLs that are required to run the widget class, some placeholder layout HTML used by the IDE and IDE property definitions.\">[PhysicalWidgetName]</a></em></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5442726\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5442726\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "web.ini Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Mai 02, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 The web.ini file defines the physical UX web widget definitions where every section is a single widget definition. Each widget definition includes the name of the widget class that implements the client (browser) side of the widget, the JavaScript, Module, and CSS files that are required to run the widget class, some placeholder layout HTML used by the IDE and IDE property definitions, IncludeScript which refers to the widget specific ProcScript or JavaScript fragments to be included and the Interface Version using which the widget is implemented. Default Location Depends on the value specified by the /adm switch. The web.ini file is located in /uniface/adm in your Uniface installation folder. File Sections [PhysicalWidgetName] Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}